line_1: And sea-nymphs are her maids of honour;
line_2: Neptune is call'd to wait upon her,

line_1: "And speaken every dele to myne honoure,
line_2: "Mich wele, grete clerk, betide thy parting houre! "

line_1: That on an Occasion so much to my Honour,
line_2: I hop'd she'd excuse me for calling upon her.
Draws ev'ry living thing upon her.

line_1: T' expose the tempter of her honour —
line_2: This you will say was well done on her

line_1: As she was a Maid of Honour,
line_2: To confer his Blessing on her.
